      • filterByCurrentWeek

        private void filterByCurrentWeek​(javafx.collections.ObservableList aList)
        The filter appointments by the current week method.

        Lambda usage: A lambda expression is used here because the original method uses a prepared SQL statement which was inefficient. We use a filtered list here which results in an "always true" predicate which is more efficient in it's use in this class and uses less lines of code making this method easily readable. This method is primarily used in the weekRadio() method. This method filters the given list based on the contents of the appointments table and by the current day and end of the week.

        Parameters:
        aList - the appointments list

      • filterByCurrentMonth

        private void filterByCurrentMonth​(javafx.collections.ObservableList aList)
        The filter appointments by the current month method.

        Lambda usage: Just like the filterByCurrentWeek() method, a lambda expression is used here because the original method uses a prepared SQL statement which was inefficient. We use a filtered list here which results in an "always true" predicate which is more efficient in it's use in this class and uses less lines of code making this method easily readable. This method is primarily used in the monthRadio() method. This method filters the given list based on the contents of the appointments table and by the current day and end of the month.

        Parameters:
        aList - the appointments list
